The paper discusses planning for ad hoc teamwork, which involves agents collaborating without prior coordination or communication. This is a problem in multiagent settings, which suggests that the paper could belong to the categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) or cs.MA (Multiagent Systems). The paper also discusses individual decision making in multiagent settings, which involves reasoning about other agents' actions, suggesting that it could belong to the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the use of interactive dynamic influence diagrams, which are a type of decision-theoretic model, suggesting that it could belong to the category of cs.GT (Game Theory) or cs.SY (Systems and Control). Overall, the most likely categories are cs.AI and cs.MA, followed by cs.LG, cs.GT, and cs.SY.
